title: For Sale/Trade:  Brazilian Mauser model 08/34 .30
postcontent:
I have for sale a Brazilian Mauser model 08/34.30 in 30-06 caliber.  The gun is in decent shape and fires good.  Both the stock and barrel have been painted back.  The serial numbers on the barrel and bolt do not match.  

If you are interested I can send pictures.  

Below is more information on the Brazilian Mausers:
The 08/34.30 started life as a contract short rifle built by CZ/Brno for Brazil. 
Original caliber was 7x57 and the contract began in 1934.
It's pretty similar looking to the VZ24 short rifle.
Some say that there were Brazilian-made actions used on some of the 08/34.30s since they lacked the usual CZ markings.

Sometime post-WWII, Brazil adopted the .30-06 as their service cartridge so these 08/34s were converted to this caliber. The original barrels were rebored/rechambered at the Fabrica De Itajuba Brasil arsenal...which later became known as IMBEL. These barrels had a ".30" stamped at the end of the 08/34 to designate that they were .30-06 models.

postcontent: Winchester Model 25 12 gauge pump – This shotgun is almost identical to the Model 12, except it does not break down in the middle and is slightly lighter for that reason. The Model 25 was only manufactured from ’49-’54 as a way to keep costs of manufacture down compared to the slightly heavier Model 12. It offers the same milled receiver and was still too costly to build to compete with the stamped Remington 870. The Model 25 was only manufactured in 12 gauge and this full choked model has a 28” barrel and has a super smooth action. If you’re a Winchester collector, this is a must have in original condition.
